1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on unsupervised modeling of morphological families in language vocabulary. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper uses contrastive estimation and log-linear models for training the model. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with unsupervised learning of language structures. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a less likely category as the paper does not explicitly mention the use of neural networks or evolutionary algorithms. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a less likely category as the paper does not focus on developing new algorithms or data structures, but rather on applying existing ones to a specific problem.
